Apparently, this was the short film that later would inspire Arrebato, by the same director. Arrebato, by the way, is here > http://thepiratebay.se/tor/4255584/Arrebato_(1979)

The film has no dialog, hence no subs, except for a quick scene in which from a telephone comes a recorded voice stating the time now (as in \"at the sound of the bell the time will be bla bla bla).

Some specs:
640*400
1500 kbps video xvid
192 kbps audio ac3


The image and sound quality is rather nice, for a film made on 16mm (and not super 8 as i initially though).

Enjoy!
